						<summary>

						<p>On the north wall, central shrine, Maṇavāḷēśvara temple.</p>						

						<p><hi rend="bold">Year 4: 975 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records a gift of a silver plate weighing 400 <hi rend="italic">kaḻañju</hi> as weighed by the <hi rend="italic">ūrkkāl</hi> to god Tiruvēḻvikkuḍi-Mahādēva, by Ayyaṉ Mārasiṅgaṉ <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Vīraśēkhara-Mūvēndavēḷāṉ of Guṇamalaippāḍi in Nallāṟṟūr-nāḍu on the northern bank of the river Kāvēri. The body <hi rend="italic">śrī-karaṇattār</hi> was entrusted with the protection of this benefaction.</p>						

						<p>Published in <hi rend="italic">S.I.I.,</hi> Vol. XIX No. 107.</p>						

						</summary>
